techmeme.title: Sources: TechInsights took apart at least one of Huawei's latest AI chips and found an Ascend 910B made by TSMC, which says it stopped Huawei shipments in 2020 (Mackenzie Hawkins/Bloomberg)
GM reports Cruise lost $435M in Q3 2024, down from a $791M loss in Q3 2023, and had $26M in net sales and revenue and $442M in total costs and expenses (Andrew J. Hawkins/The Verge)
Stability AI releases Stable Diffusion 3.5 Large, an 8B-parameter model that makes 1MP images, and 3.5 Large Turbo, and plans to launch 3.5 Medium on October 29 (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
Anthropic claims that its new Sonnet 3.5 model scores 49% on SWE-bench Verified, up from 33.4% and "higher than all" public models, and debuts Claude 3.5 Haiku (Anthropic)
Anthropic releases a new Claude 3.5 Sonnet model that can interact with desktop apps by imitating mouse and keyboard input via a "computer use" API, now in beta (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
